{"id":"1412.1801","submitter":"Andrea Petrucci","authors":"F. Cardone, R. Mignani, A. Petrucci","title":"Metric Gauge Fields in Deformed Special Relativity","comments":"20 pages, 1 figure","journal-ref":"EJTP 10, No. 29 (2013) 1-20 Electronic Journal of Theoretical\n  Physics","doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"physics.gen-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We show that, in the framework of Deformed Special Relativity (DSR), namely a\n(four-dimensional) generalization of the (local) space-time struc- ture based\non an energy-dependent \"deformation\" of the usual Minkowski geometry, two kinds\nof gauge symmetries arise, whose spaces either coin- cide with the deformed\nMinkowski space or are just internal spaces to it. This is why we named them\n\"metric gauge theories\". In the case of the internal gauge fields, they are a\nconsequence of the deformed Minkowski space (DMS) possessing the structure of a\ngeneralized Lagrange space. Such a geometrical structure allows one to define\ncurvature and torsion in the DMS.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 29 May 2013 12:42:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-31"}
